            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Distrubed Rest",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "One of the most common ways for a poltergeist to form is when its burial site is desecrated by the construction of a dwelling. This is usually an accident, but some evil creatures seek out such burial sites, intentionally creating poltergeists to serve as guardians.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 264
                    },
                    "subtype": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Poltergeist Treasure",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "A poltergeist needs items to hurl as weapons, and over the centuries of use, only durable objects survive its rampages. Silver dinnerware, hatchets, and books might all be found in a poltergeist\u2019s collection.",
